articles.title: AWS Lambda
articles.content: AWS Lambda is a compute service that lets you run code without provisioning or managing servers. Lambda handles all the administration of the underlying infrastructure, including server and operating system maintenance, capacity provisioning, and automatic scaling. All you need to do is supply your code in one of the languages that Lambda supports. Lambda runs your code on a high-availability compute infrastructure and performs all of the administration of the compute resources, including server and operating system maintenance, automatic scaling and code monitoring, capacity provisioning, and code logging. Lambda is a perfect fit for many applications, including back-end web services, mobile back ends, and processing data streams. Lambda can also be used for IoT applications, gaming applications, and data-processing applications.

articles.title: Amazon AWS
articles.content: AWS is a secure cloud services platform, offering compute power, database storage, content delivery and other functionality to help businesses scale and grow. One of the key benefits of AWS is its security. AWS provides a number of features to help keep your data safe, including data encryption, identity and access management, and robust networking and security controls.
